3.7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[203,368,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phyllopterini">Phyllopterini</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[374,750,1518,1544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 401" refId="ref29469" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1878) Monographie der Phaneropteriden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 28, 1 - 401." type="journal article" year="1878">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1590,1724]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
This taxon was recently elevated to tribe status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[719,1024,1590,1617]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="217 - 261" refId="ref29990" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2015 c) Las tribus Phyllopterini n. stat. y Plagiopleurini n. stat. &amp; n. sensu (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae): Octavo aporte a la organizacion supragenerica de los faneropterinos neotropicales. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa (S. E. A.), 57, 217 - 261." type="journal article" year="2015">Cadena-Castañeda (2015c)</bibRefCitation>
, which provided keys to its two subtribes, as well as to 14 genera. This tribe currently presents 117 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[943,1185,1626,1652]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[1047,1102,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
. This is the first record of the tribe for the 
<collectingRegion box="[372,516,1662,1688]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, and here we recorded three genera and six species, both from the Phyllopterina subtribe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
